ResumeParserData.Experience: SENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEERING MANAGER, PORCH  Seattle, WA - 10/2018 - Present  Lead many different teams as the result of business' changes of directions and engineering reorgs. At one point, led three engineering teams. Currently leading two engineering teams supporting two business units of two separate business groups / companies : the Referral Network (home services referral) , and the Porch Managed Services (handyman services) .  SOME HIGHLIGHTS  Leading the GAAP and SOX compliance work for the Referral BU. Together with other leaders, helping build and document compliance controls and policies.  Work closely with Product, Operation, and business leaders to plan the roadmaps, projects, and resources for my teams.  Improve processes of how product and engineering efficiently work together (epic kickoff, scrumming, event storming, etc.) .  Grow teams. Build a strong agile culture of trust, psychological safety, team collaboration, knowledge sharing, growth, coaching, and mentorship. Remove silos.  Improve monitors and alerts of our systems. Constantly addressing technical debts, improving the systems' sustainability, operational excellence, performance, security, testability, and cost optimization.  Started the design review culture to help make sure that we build the right thing the right way.  Started the documentation culture and continuously expanding our knowledge base documentation.  Work with outstanding performers to promote them to the next engineering levels. Identify potential leaders and coach them to the management path if they are interested. I have mentored, coached, and promoted 2 senior engineers to managers here at Porch.  An advocate for the internship program, the quarterly hackathon, and the DEI at work.  Managed remote teams in Sunnyvale, California, Heredia, Costa Rica, and Gujarat, India. Built the Costa Rica squad from scratch in 3 months.  Supported the company, led my teams through the layoff, followed by the furlough due to the impact of COVID-19 and the industry situation. Helped bring back people after the furlough and reorganized resources to teams.  Our stack : JVM : Scala, Kotlin, Java, .NET : C#, Javascript, TypeScript, ReactJS, Node.js, ASP.NET MVC, PostgreSQL, MS SQL, AWS, GCP, Docker, Kubernetes    MANAGER OF APPLICATION DEVELOPMENT, THRIFTBOOKS  Tukwila, WA - 03/2018 - 08/2018  Led the ThriftBooks' Application Team. I helped change how the team worked from a siloed, randomized team to a more collaborative, focused, reliable, and agile team.  Removed silos. Worked closely with POs as I changed the process.  Taught, trained team on Agile practices : effective stand-ups, writing good stories, story decomposition and sizing, creating TACs, retrospectives, etc.  Initiated and led the effort of decomposing, refactoring some large and troublesome applications of the system. Participated in making architectural design decisions. Taught my team to use the strangler pattern to introduce new architecture to the system.  Created the new process for handling service desk tickets to reduce the randomization to help my team focused on sprint tasks.  Improved existing home-brewed monitoring system. Introduced using NewRelics to monitor the system for performance and errors.  Enforced unit testing of new code. Introduced VSTS Test Manager to capture test cases for components of the system and trained my team to develop the habit of running the test cases.  Centralized logging with the Elastic Stack. Single-handedly researched, prototyped, deployed it, and converted two important applications to using it which made analyzing logs faster, more reliable, and reduce stress on the monolith database.  Hired, onboarded new hires.    SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT MANAGER, QUALTRICS  Seattle, WA - 05/2017 - 03/2018  Led the CORE Services team while also performing the roles of a TPM, an architect, and a principal Individual Contributor.  Brought structure and order to a randomized and disconnected CORE Services team of 4 senior engineers. Grew the team to a strongly bonded, collaborative, and self- organized unit of 10 engineers in less than a quarter.  Led and managed multiple cross-team projects.  Redesigned a couple of legacy microservices to replace the backend data storage from HBase to other DB technologies as well as to simplify them. Joined with another engineer to implement the changes.  Constantly learned the technology stack we used and the microservices the team owned. Implemented bug fixes and added features to existing microservices.  Participated in Design Office Hour meetings, and provided feedback on designs, and solutions presented by other teams.  Participated in the weekly Ops meetings to help improve the system support, maintenance, and operations.  Supported other teams when they needed help with our services.    DMTS SOFTWARE ARCHITECT & ENGINEERING MANAGER, MOTOROLA SOLUTIONS, INC.  Seattle, WA - 07/2010 - 05/2017  A key member of the Seattle Design Center Leadership Team, a DTMS software architect, a technical lead, later transitioned to an Engineering Manager.  Designed / architected projects developed at the Seattle Design Center as well as managed the engineering team responsible for the WAVE on Cloud product.  Worked closely with the TPMs, the product owners, the chief architect, and engineering directors on projects initiated by the Seattle Design Center.  Grew a team starting from 2 contractors to 6 FTE and 3 contractors. On-boarded new hires while still doing other technical work. Helped make my team a self-organized unit.  Led the WAVE on Cloud project : designed the SaaS solution to integrate land mobile radio (LMR) with broadband using WAVE software, led the development effort, streamlined the process of configuring WAVE software to work with radio systems, constant interactions with Dev Ops when preparing for launch on AWS, explored / learned AWS : IoT, Lambda, API Gateway, DynamoDB, serverless framework, and many other AWS services to apply them to the design.  Integrated WAVE with Intelligent Middleware (IMW) : IMW is the data-centric platform / bridge. This project was the first attempt to publish location data of mobile clients in WAVE to ASTRO radio system. Designed and implemented the solution with another colleague. Actively contributed to the evolution of IMW.  Coached team members on software engineering best practices, test automation, software design and patterns, and agile software development.  STAFF PRINCIPAL SOFTWARE ENGINEER / DEV LEAD  Led the web and services team that was responsible for WAVE 3000 and WAVE Connection products.  WAVE 3000 server to support Capacity Plus (CP) and Linked Capacity Plus (LCP) radio systems. Quickly learned how CP/LCP radio system works. Designed the integration work. Implemented many important areas of the solution. Later, also helped design and implement WAVE 5000 product to support CP/LCP radio systems.  Provided technical guidance and led the team to successful releases of the WAVE 3000 product.  LEAD SENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEER  Built the team to work on the Motorola Anywhere Gateway product, the first hardware product ever shipped by Twisted Pair Solutions (the name of the company before becoming Motorola Solutions Inc.) . Together with other team members, designed and implemented the solution. Led the team to the successful release of the product which contributed to MSI considering Twisted Pair Solutions for acquisition.  Member of the initial development team of the WAVE Connections project, the first SaaS offering of WAVE software by Twisted Pair Solutions, designed and implemented more than half of the solution. Then started leading the effort of rebuilding the team. Improved, enhanced the code base, and successfully launched the solution on AWS. Introduced TDD, CI/CD to the team and made them team agreements.  Enhanced, bug-fixed WAVE desktop communicators which are widely deployed applications with thousands of clients in daily use around the world supporting critical communications for the military, federal government and commercial organizations.  Designed and implemented the new WAVE communicator that can integrate into Microsoft Lync, SharePoint, or run in the browser using Silverlight, Lync SDK, UCMA SDK and Bing Maps SDK. The first WAVE communicator that employs map and displays locations of WAVE users on the map.    SR. SOFTWARE ENGINEER, AREVA T&D  Redmond, WA - 04/2007 - 07/2010  Worked in the R&D UI team on maintaining and enhancing FG Display Builder, e- terrabrowser (ETB) , the feature-rich AREVA T&Ds web-based full graphics display development toolkit with a mixture of old and new technologies, e-terravision (ETV) , a WPF app, an operator-friendly system that enables power dispatchers to fully visualize their networks and to proactively operate the grid by taking the necessary real-time corrective actions. Some of the highlights :   Proposed using modern WPF controls in FG Display Builder, a MFC app and ETB, a WinForm app. Designed and implemented the approved proposal. Lead engineer of the development work.  Implemented calling up the station's one-line display by drag and drop it from ETV to ETB.  Pioneered the effort of using TestComplete to automate the testing of ETV.  Proposed, designed, and implemented the idea of adding record and replay to ETB to use for automating the acceptance testing of the product.  Introduced TDD to the team. Worked with and overcame resistance from some team members.  Identified and fixed many major memory leaks in ETV (WPF) and ETB (WinForm) .    SOFTWARE DEVELOPER (SPECIALIST) , WEYERHAEUSER  Federal Way, WA - 08/2005 - 04/2007  Worked in the Web Services team building Weyerhaeuser's e-commerce website and the FileNet Imaging team designing and developing software solutions to feed data to the FileNet system.  Automated CI/CD with NAnt  Integrated the Packaging business's backend sale systems to existing online MyWey Order Service system (MOS) to allow a new order workflow for Packaging customers. Coached by Net Objectives on Agile Software Development.  Refactored many ASP.NET WebForm pages of the MOS application to using the MVP design pattern to facilitate unit testing and TDD.  Started learning and applying unit testing and TDD as well as SCRUM.  Received Weyerhaeuser Service Excellence Award.    SOFTWARE ENGINEER II, HONEYWELL AEROSPACE  Redmond, WA - 12/2004 - 08/2005  Worked in the IHAS team on the Airbus A380s Aircraft Environment Surveillance System (AESS) , an integrated solution platform comprised of the Enhanced Ground Proximity Warning System (EGPWS) , Traffic Collision Avoidance System (TCAS) , Mode-S Transponder and Weather Radar, using C++ in accordance with DO-178B.  Optimized, cleaned up, bug fixed IOM and AESS shared codes.  Using Enterprise Architect, reverse engineered existing code to create UML class diagrams for documenting purposes. Also created sequence diagrams for many functional areas.  Code reviewed, tracked, and verified code changes using DOORS.  The Build Master of the team    SOFTWARE DEVELOPER (SPECIALIST) , WEYERHAEUSER  Federal Way - 01/2001 - 12/2004  Joined the Application Engineering department out of college. Participated in many projects of different scales and gained lots of experience from talented individuals in the team. Later, became a member of the initial FileNet Imaging team when Weyerhaeuser'started moving toward electronic document management.    SOFTWARE DEVELOPER INTERN, WEYERHAEUSER  Federal Way, WA - 01/2000 - 12/2000  As an intern with only the knowledge of C++ and Java, I participated in the Company's Online Telephone Directory project which required ASP, VB6 and T-SQL. I learned the basics of those in a few weeks then learned on the go. Contributed a great deal to the success of the project and was offered a job before the internship ended.  COMPUTER SUPPORT TECHNICIAN I, COMPUTING CENTER OF SEATTLE CENTRAL COLLEGE  Seattle, WA - 09/1996 - 12/1999  Supported students in the computer lab by answering application questions and troubleshooting technical issues.  TUTOR, STUDENT ACADEMIC ASSISTANT OF SEATTLE CENTRAL COLLEGE  Seattle, WA - 09/1997-03/1999  Tutored C and C++, Math from algebra to calculus (MATH 123 to MATH 126) , and all Physics levels.

Summary
A deeply people-focused technology leader who offers expertise in building and scaling highly performant engineering teams to support business objectives. Experience
SENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEERING MANAGER, PORCH
Seattle, WA - 10/2018 - Present
Lead many different teams as the result of business' changes of directions and engineering reorgs. At one point, led three engineering teams. Currently leading two engineering teams supporting two business units of two separate business groups/companies : the Referral Network (home services referral) , and the Porch Managed Services (handyman services) .
SOME HIGHLIGHTS
Leading the GAAP and SOX compliance work for the Referral BU. Together with other leaders, helping build and document compliance controls and policies.
Work closely with Product, Operation, and business leaders to plan the roadmaps, projects, and resources for my teams.
Improve processes of how product and engineering efficiently work together (epic kickoff, scrumming, event storming, etc.) .
Grow teams. Build a strong agile culture of trust, psychological safety, team collaboration, knowledge sharing, growth, coaching, and mentorship. Remove silos.
Improve monitors and alerts of our systems. Constantly addressing technical debts, improving the systems' sustainability, operational excellence, performance, security, testability, and cost optimization.
Started the design review culture to help make sure that we build the right thing the right way.
Started the documentation culture and continuously expanding our knowledge base documentation.
Work with outstanding performers to promote them to the next engineering levels. Identify potential leaders and coach them to the management path if they are interested. I have mentored, coached, and promoted 2 senior engineers to managers here at Porch.
An advocate for the internship program, the quarterly hackathon, and the DEI at work.
Managed remote teams in Sunnyvale, California, Heredia, Costa Rica, and Gujarat, India. Built the Costa Rica squad from scratch in 3 months.
Supported the company, led my teams through the layoff, followed by the furlough due to the impact of COVID-19 and the industry situation. Helped bring back people after the furlough and reorganized resources to teams.
Our stack : JVM : Scala, Kotlin, Java, .NET : C#, Javascript, TypeScript, ReactJS, Node.js, ASP.NET MVC, PostgreSQL, MS SQL, AWS, GCP, Docker, Kubernetes

MANAGER OF APPLICATION DEVELOPMENT, THRIFTBOOKS
Tukwila, WA - 03/2018 - 08/2018
Led the ThriftBooks' Application Team. I helped change how the team worked from a siloed, randomized team to a more collaborative, focused, reliable, and agile team.
Removed silos. Worked closely with POs as I changed the process.
Taught, trained team on Agile practices : effective stand-ups, writing good stories, story decomposition and sizing, creating TACs, retrospectives, etc.
Initiated and led the effort of decomposing, refactoring some large and troublesome applications of the system. Participated in making architectural design decisions. Taught my team to use the strangler pattern to introduce new architecture to the system.
Created the new process for handling service desk tickets to reduce the randomization to help my team focused on sprint tasks.
Improved existing home-brewed monitoring system. Introduced using NewRelics to monitor the system for performance and errors.
Enforced unit testing of new code. Introduced VSTS Test Manager to capture test cases for components of the system and trained my team to develop the habit of running the test cases.
Centralized logging with the Elastic Stack. Single-handedly researched, prototyped, deployed it, and converted two important applications to using it which made analyzing logs faster, more reliable, and reduce stress on the monolith database.
Hired, onboarded new hires.

SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT MANAGER, QUALTRICS
Seattle, WA - 05/2017 - 03/2018
Led the CORE Services team while also performing the roles of a TPM, an architect, and a principal Individual Contributor.
Brought structure and order to a randomized and disconnected CORE Services team of 4 senior engineers. Grew the team to a strongly bonded, collaborative, and self- organized unit of 10 engineers in less than a quarter.
Led and managed multiple cross-team projects.
Redesigned a couple of legacy microservices to replace the backend data storage from HBase to other DB technologies as well as to simplify them. Joined with another engineer to implement the changes.
Constantly learned the technology stack we used and the microservices the team owned. Implemented bug fixes and added features to existing microservices.
Participated in Design Office Hour meetings, and provided feedback on designs, and solutions presented by other teams.
Participated in the weekly Ops meetings to help improve the system support, maintenance, and operations.
Supported other teams when they needed help with our services.

DMTS SOFTWARE ARCHITECT & ENGINEERING MANAGER, MOTOROLA SOLUTIONS, INC.
Seattle, WA - 07/2010 - 05/2017
A key member of the Seattle Design Center Leadership Team, a DTMS software architect, a technical lead, later transitioned to an Engineering Manager.
Designed/architected projects developed at the Seattle Design Center as well as managed the engineering team responsible for the WAVE on Cloud product.
Worked closely with the TPMs, the product owners, the chief architect, and engineering directors on projects initiated by the Seattle Design Center.
Grew a team starting from 2 contractors to 6 FTE and 3 contractors. On-boarded new hires while still doing other technical work. Helped make my team a self-organized unit.
Led the WAVE on Cloud project : designed the SaaS solution to integrate land mobile radio (LMR) with broadband using WAVE software, led the development effort, streamlined the process of configuring WAVE software to work with radio systems, constant interactions with Dev Ops when preparing for launch on AWS, explored/learned AWS IoT, Lambda, API Gateway, DynamoDB, serverless framework, and many other AWS services to apply them to the design.
Integrated WAVE with Intelligent Middleware (IMW) : IMW is the data-centric platform/bridge. This project was the first attempt to publish location data of mobile clients in WAVE to ASTRO radio system. Designed and implemented the solution with another colleague. STAFF PRINCIPAL SOFTWARE ENGINEER/DEV LEAD

Provided technical guidance and led the team to successful releases of the WAVE 3000 product.
LEAD SENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEER
Built the team to work on the Motorola Anywhere Gateway product, the first hardware product ever shipped by Twisted Pair Solutions (the name of the company before becoming Motorola Solutions Inc.) . Together with other team members, designed and implemented the solution. Led the team to the successful release of the product which contributed to MSI considering Twisted Pair Solutions for acquisition.
Member of the initial development team of the WAVE Connections project, the first SaaS offering of WAVE software by Twisted Pair Solutions, designed and implemented more than half of the solution. Introduced TDD, CI/CD to the team and made them team agreements.
Enhanced, bug-fixed WAVE desktop communicators which are widely deployed applications with thousands of clients in daily use around the world supporting critical communications for the military, federal government and commercial organizations.
Designed and implemented the new WAVE communicator that can integrate into Microsoft Lync, SharePoint, or run in the browser using Silverlight, Lync SDK, UCMA SDK and Bing Maps SDK. The first WAVE communicator that employs map and displays locations of WAVE users on the map.

Automated CI/CD with NAnt

Started learning and applying unit testing and TDD as well as SCRUM.
Received Weyerhaeuser Service Excellence Award.
